WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:08.747
- Previously
on "Briarpatch"...

00:08.791 --> 00:11.446
This town is full of unsolved
goddamn explosions.

00:12.882 --> 00:15.232
- That was you, wasn't it?
- You know I have an alibi.

00:15.276 --> 00:18.714
- For the second bomb.
There was a second bomber.

00:18.757 --> 00:20.107
[yelps]

00:20.150 --> 00:22.326
- You're gonna die out here.
You know that, right?

00:22.370 --> 00:24.459
- [grunts]
- [screams]

00:24.502 --> 00:27.288
- The person who killed
Felicity is Gene Colder.

00:27.331 --> 00:29.116
He was Brattle's inside man.

00:29.159 --> 00:31.814
- If Felicity
really wanted help,

00:31.857 --> 00:33.642
she would've called someone.

00:33.685 --> 00:36.079
- She did call someone.
- We have to talk.

00:36.123 --> 00:38.299
I need help.
Meet me in Packingtown.

00:38.342 --> 00:40.083
- Any idea
who she was talking to?

00:40.127 --> 00:41.650
- Someone she thought
she could trust.

00:41.693 --> 00:43.739
- Chief Raytek, when you come
to me for a favor,

00:43.782 --> 00:45.784
make sure you bring something
of equal or greater value

00:45.828 --> 00:47.743
to exchange.

00:47.786 --> 00:49.571
Well, well, well...

00:49.614 --> 00:52.574
This should take care
of your problem.

00:52.617 --> 00:53.618
- [groans]

00:53.662 --> 00:55.098
- Would it be a problem

00:55.142 --> 00:58.406
if Ms. Dill never went back
to Washington?

00:58.449 --> 01:00.843
- New plan--we're gonna hand
him over to justice,

01:00.886 --> 01:03.759
no strings attached, and, hell,
they can have Spivey, too.

01:03.802 --> 01:05.935
- You do understand
what Brattle meant

01:05.978 --> 01:06.936
about Allegra.

01:06.979 --> 01:07.937
And you're okay with it?

01:07.980 --> 01:09.243
- Okay with it?

01:09.286 --> 01:11.767
I'm gonna be
the fucking president.

01:11.810 --> 01:12.898
- What are we gonna do?

01:12.942 --> 01:16.206
[dramatic drumbeats]

01:16.250 --> 01:18.034
- We're gonna take them
all down.

01:18.078 --> 01:21.124
♪

01:22.560 --> 01:24.562
- ♪ My gal is red hot

01:24.606 --> 01:25.998
- ♪ Your gal
ain't doodly-squat ♪

01:26.042 --> 01:27.043
- ♪ Yeah

01:27.087 --> 01:29.306
♪ My gal is red hot

01:29.350 --> 01:30.699
- ♪ Your gal
ain't doodly-squat ♪

01:30.742 --> 01:32.266
- ♪ Well,
she ain't got no money ♪

01:32.309 --> 01:35.486
♪ But, man,
she's really got a lot ♪

01:35.530 --> 01:38.533
♪ Well, I've got a gal,
6 feet 4 ♪

01:38.576 --> 01:40.404
♪ Sleeps in the kitchen
with her feets out the door ♪

01:40.448 --> 01:43.407
♪ But my gal is red hot

01:43.451 --> 01:44.756
- ♪ Your gal
ain't doodly-squat ♪

01:44.800 --> 01:45.583
- ♪ Yeah

01:45.627 --> 01:48.020
♪ My gal is red hot

01:48.064 --> 01:49.761
- ♪ Your gal
ain't doodly-squat ♪

01:49.805 --> 01:51.241
♪ Well,
she ain't got no money ♪

01:51.285 --> 01:54.940
♪ But, man,
she's really got a lot ♪

01:54.984 --> 01:56.768
♪ Well...

01:56.812 --> 02:03.775
♪

02:10.217 --> 02:13.220
- ♪ Whoa

02:13.263 --> 02:16.092
♪ Whoa

02:16.136 --> 02:19.095
♪ Whoa

02:19.139 --> 02:25.884
♪

02:25.928 --> 02:28.974
♪ I objected

02:29.018 --> 02:30.846
♪ When they took it

02:33.196 --> 02:35.894
- This is the one
that makes me rich.

02:35.938 --> 02:38.984
- Yeah, Felicity's
life insurance policy.

02:39.028 --> 02:41.248
And the one in the green folder
is the power of attorney

02:41.291 --> 02:42.640
that makes me rich

02:42.684 --> 02:44.773
if you go through
with this fool-ass plan

02:44.816 --> 02:46.427
and get yourself killed.

02:49.952 --> 02:51.780
[tense music]

02:51.823 --> 02:53.825
- We're doing this...

02:53.869 --> 02:55.262
now.

02:55.305 --> 02:59.091
- The Dill ladies are never
lacking in confidence.

02:59.135 --> 03:01.833
All right.
Explain it to me...

03:01.877 --> 03:04.009
in detail.

03:04.053 --> 03:07.187
♪

03:07.230 --> 03:10.581
- Every minute of their lives
moving forward

03:10.625 --> 03:12.104
they are gonna owe to me.

03:12.148 --> 03:14.063
- You do understand
what Brattle meant

03:14.106 --> 03:15.238
about Allegra.

03:15.282 --> 03:17.588
- Yeah.
- And you're okay with it?

03:17.632 --> 03:20.287
- Okay with it?
I'm gonna be the fucking pre--

03:20.330 --> 03:21.723
- Hot damn.

03:21.766 --> 03:22.680
That's our ticket out.

03:22.724 --> 03:26.336
We got a United States
senator...

03:26.380 --> 03:27.946
dead to rights.

03:27.990 --> 03:30.122
Immunity?
Boy, did I aim low.

03:30.166 --> 03:32.995
This dude gets
in the White House,

03:33.038 --> 03:37.042
I might end up the ambassador
to fucking Bora Bora.

03:37.086 --> 03:39.219
[laughs]

03:43.962 --> 03:46.487
Oh, please, not that look.

03:46.530 --> 03:50.621
- This tape
is our ticket to Gene Colder.

03:50.665 --> 03:54.364
- Oh, no.

03:54.408 --> 03:56.148
- And how do you think
Jake Spivey's gonna react

03:56.192 --> 03:59.717
to that?

03:59.761 --> 04:01.153
- Not real well.

04:01.197 --> 04:02.546
- God damn it.

04:02.590 --> 04:05.114
Look, I got the IRS sniffing
at everything I own.

04:05.157 --> 04:07.116
I got the FBI
breathing down my neck.

04:07.159 --> 04:08.683
The immunity's off the table.

04:08.726 --> 04:11.686
That tape there,
that fixes all of that.

04:11.729 --> 04:15.211
That's the ultimate briarpatch
right there.

04:15.255 --> 04:16.691
Besides, how you think

04:16.734 --> 04:18.736
you gonna trade that
for Colder?

04:18.780 --> 04:20.782
It's been a whole day.
He's in the wind.

04:20.825 --> 04:23.959
- There's someone
who can blow him back this way.

04:25.830 --> 04:27.179
- No.

04:27.223 --> 04:28.920
- No.

04:28.964 --> 04:30.487
- Yes.

04:30.531 --> 04:33.403
Clyde Brattle
can bring me Colder, Jake.

04:34.752 --> 04:36.319
We give him the tape
in exchange.

04:36.363 --> 04:39.148
- No way!

04:39.191 --> 04:41.150
He does not get to win.

04:41.193 --> 04:42.586
You said so yourself.

04:42.630 --> 04:44.936
- You're doing this...

04:44.980 --> 04:46.808
for me.

04:49.332 --> 04:52.117
You've done bad things, Jake.

04:52.161 --> 04:54.076
We both have.

04:54.119 --> 04:56.252
We have to make it right...

04:56.296 --> 04:57.688
for Felicity.

05:00.387 --> 05:03.912
- [sighs]

05:03.955 --> 05:08.220
So, what, I'm looking
at a couple years?

05:08.264 --> 05:09.744
Right?

05:12.399 --> 05:14.357
Still got my land.

05:19.406 --> 05:22.670
It's just that, uh...

05:22.713 --> 05:26.717
you know, after the way
we left things yesterday...

05:26.761 --> 05:29.503
I've been
kind of wondering if...

05:31.679 --> 05:34.464
We still understood each other.

05:34.508 --> 05:37.380
- I'm the person
who knows you best.

05:38.947 --> 05:40.340
Remember?

05:43.386 --> 05:46.128
- Yeah, I'm in.

05:46.171 --> 05:48.130
What's the move?

05:48.173 --> 05:49.827
- The San Bonifacio
Police Department

05:49.871 --> 05:52.047
is reporting no progress
in the hunt

05:52.090 --> 05:53.353
for the high-school-reunion
bomber.

05:53.396 --> 05:54.745
[door creaks open]

05:54.789 --> 05:56.834
The whereabouts
of Captain Eugene Colder...

05:56.878 --> 05:58.009
[door closes]

05:58.053 --> 05:59.359
Hailed as a hero
by Chief Eve Raytek,

05:59.402 --> 06:00.708
remain unknown.

06:00.751 --> 06:02.753
Services for fallen sergeant
Henry Mock

06:02.797 --> 06:04.842
are scheduled for tomorrow.

06:04.886 --> 06:06.148
Temperatures today
are expected

06:06.191 --> 06:08.585
to remain north
of 100 degrees...

06:08.629 --> 06:11.545
[tense music]

06:11.588 --> 06:18.726
♪

06:20.815 --> 06:22.469
- [sighs]

06:22.512 --> 06:24.993
Thank God you're alive.

06:25.036 --> 06:25.994
[gun thuds]

06:26.037 --> 06:27.952
[sighs] Coffee?

06:29.737 --> 06:31.739
- You break up with Raytek.
- [exhales sharply]

06:31.782 --> 06:33.654
- Tell her the plan is off.

06:33.697 --> 06:36.396
- She ain't gonna be too happy
about that.

06:36.439 --> 06:37.614
What the hell
am I supposed to say?

06:37.658 --> 06:40.095
- Don't say a goddamn thing.

06:41.444 --> 06:43.185
- Immunity's off the table.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.885
And I'm going to prison.

06:47.929 --> 06:50.105
- I don't get it, Jake.
What changed?

06:50.148 --> 06:51.411
- I guess you could say

06:51.454 --> 06:54.849
that I'm ready
to take my medicine.

06:54.892 --> 06:56.894
- Jake, you're about as ready
to take your medicine

06:56.938 --> 06:59.027
as a goddamn
Christian Scientist.

06:59.070 --> 07:02.552
We're partners here.
You can level with me.

07:02.596 --> 07:04.902
[sighs] God damn it,
I care about you.

07:04.946 --> 07:08.950
[chuckles]
- It's Pick, okay?

07:08.993 --> 07:10.212
I owe her.

07:10.255 --> 07:11.735
Maybe some good

07:11.779 --> 07:14.477
can come out
of this whole mess.

07:16.044 --> 07:17.306
More than a water park.

07:17.349 --> 07:20.135
- That water park
was a class-action lawsuit

07:20.178 --> 07:21.571
with a snack bar.

07:21.615 --> 07:24.487
It was never gonna happen.

07:24.531 --> 07:27.098
- When she hears
the state of play,

07:27.142 --> 07:29.492
she'll pivot.

07:29.536 --> 07:31.146
Pivot hard.

07:31.189 --> 07:33.061
- Jake, we are the ones

07:33.104 --> 07:35.585
who have to take care
of this town

07:35.629 --> 07:37.021
when your girlfriend's back

07:37.065 --> 07:39.110
sipping lattes
in Dupont Circle.

07:39.154 --> 07:41.199
- No.

07:41.243 --> 07:43.027
Pick ain't going back to D.C.

07:43.071 --> 07:44.812
- Oh.
Does her senator know?

07:44.855 --> 07:48.511
- [scoffs] No, he ain't long
for the place neither.

07:48.555 --> 07:50.861
Pick's got something on him.

07:50.905 --> 07:54.038
Something bad.

07:54.082 --> 07:56.301
♪

07:56.345 --> 07:59.479
- He can't help himself.

07:59.522 --> 08:03.439
- So she's trading it
to Brattle

08:03.483 --> 08:06.442
in exchange for Colder.

08:06.486 --> 08:08.531
Look, are we square?

08:08.575 --> 08:11.491
I've given you
all I could, Eve.

08:11.534 --> 08:14.450
I'm sorry it wasn't enough.

08:14.494 --> 08:17.671
- No, it was more than enough.
[refrigerator door closes]

08:17.714 --> 08:19.890
You're a good man,
Jake Spivey.

08:22.371 --> 08:24.547
- Well, thanks, Eve.

08:24.591 --> 08:27.594
You're a pretty good man
yourself.

08:27.637 --> 08:28.769
Hey, this ain't bad.

08:28.812 --> 08:30.510
- That's dog food.
- Mm-hmm.

08:32.294 --> 08:34.905
[funky music]

08:34.949 --> 08:36.907
- Okay,
but what makes you think

08:36.951 --> 08:39.997
Colder ain't sitting on a beach
in Mexico by now?

08:40.041 --> 08:42.173
- All the people he blames
for ruining his life

08:42.217 --> 08:44.001
are in this town.

08:44.045 --> 08:46.134
I don't think
he ever really left.

08:46.177 --> 08:50.225
Let's see what happens
if we bait the hook.

08:50.268 --> 08:51.966
What about his wife?

08:52.009 --> 08:54.011
Do you think she'll give us
what we need?

08:54.055 --> 08:56.231
- Who she saw Felicity meet
in Packingtown?

08:56.274 --> 08:57.711
We'll see.

08:57.754 --> 08:59.669
Visiting hours at County
start at 10:00, so...

08:59.713 --> 09:01.018
[buzzer blares]

09:01.062 --> 09:04.195
[indistinct announcement]

09:04.239 --> 09:05.545
I'm so sorry, Lucretia.

09:05.588 --> 09:07.895
- Don't be.

09:07.938 --> 09:10.506
I am guilty.

09:10.550 --> 09:12.900
I shot that man
right between his eyes.

09:12.943 --> 09:15.380
[sighs]

09:15.424 --> 09:17.513
His poor girlfriend.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.080
Christ.

09:19.123 --> 09:20.255
- Can I ask--

09:20.298 --> 09:23.911
why'd you two move here?

09:23.954 --> 09:25.695
It's never made sense to me.

09:25.739 --> 09:27.784
- It was a couple years ago.

09:27.828 --> 09:31.483
Gene kept getting home
from work later and later.

09:31.527 --> 09:32.920
I think he was in
over his head.

09:32.963 --> 09:34.878
And then one night,
he sat me down at the table,

09:34.922 --> 09:36.619
and he said,
"What about Texas?"

09:36.663 --> 09:40.014
[laughs]

09:40.057 --> 09:43.147
I had never lived west
of the Schuylkill River.

09:45.323 --> 09:47.325
But he said there would be
opportunity here.

09:47.369 --> 09:50.851
He said we could have a house.

09:50.894 --> 09:52.983
We could even have kids.

09:56.552 --> 09:59.729
I don't know why he lied...

09:59.773 --> 10:03.341
because the second we landed,
he replaced me.

10:03.385 --> 10:06.736
And I stayed because my dad
used to say to me,

10:06.780 --> 10:09.260
"You can survive anything."

10:11.959 --> 10:16.267
Why would anyone say something
so cruel to a child?

10:16.311 --> 10:18.618
- Luke...

10:18.661 --> 10:20.881
your husband is a bad man.

10:20.924 --> 10:22.491
[brakes squeak]

10:22.534 --> 10:24.580
[tense music]

10:24.624 --> 10:26.887
He's a murderer.

10:26.930 --> 10:29.063
He killed Felicity Dill

10:29.106 --> 10:31.065
and kept you drugged
and so spun around

10:31.108 --> 10:32.414
that you killed somebody, too.

10:32.457 --> 10:35.983
I know the truth
can be painful...

10:36.026 --> 10:38.463
and I don't want to cause you
more suffering,

10:38.507 --> 10:40.248
but you deserve to know.

10:40.291 --> 10:42.467
♪

10:42.511 --> 10:44.208
- Thank you.

10:44.252 --> 10:46.689
♪

10:46.733 --> 10:48.473
Thank you.

10:48.517 --> 10:49.649
[sniffles]

10:49.692 --> 10:52.739
And I need you
to tell me something.

10:52.782 --> 10:55.698
- Name it.

10:55.742 --> 10:58.353
- That he's not gonna
get away with it.

10:58.396 --> 11:01.661
- You tell me
what I need to know...

11:01.704 --> 11:04.925
and I will promise you that.

11:04.968 --> 11:06.883
- I need help.

11:06.927 --> 11:09.016
No, not there.
It's not safe.

11:09.059 --> 11:10.974
Meet me in Packingtown.

11:19.374 --> 11:22.290
[cell phone buzzing]

11:25.554 --> 11:26.816
- New plan.

11:26.860 --> 11:28.949
Screw the public hearing.

11:28.992 --> 11:30.515
Once we get all the evidence
from Brattle,

11:30.559 --> 11:32.039
we're gonna hand him over
to Justice,

11:32.082 --> 11:33.214
no strings attached,
and, hell...

11:33.257 --> 11:35.216
- Boss.
- They can have Spivey, too.

11:37.566 --> 11:39.655
- You have something I want.

11:39.699 --> 11:40.917
- Oh?

11:40.961 --> 11:42.049
- Only in person.

11:42.092 --> 11:44.312
- And why would I do that?

11:44.355 --> 11:45.661
- Because you're out
of options.

11:45.705 --> 11:48.969
The senator's gonna rat-fuck
you and Jake both.

11:49.012 --> 11:50.710
Once he has the goods
on his competition,

11:50.753 --> 11:53.713
he's turning you over
to Justice.

11:53.756 --> 11:55.671
- And?
- And...

11:55.715 --> 11:57.934
if you meet me this afternoon
and give me what I want,

11:57.978 --> 12:00.720
you can have this tape...

12:00.763 --> 12:03.244
and turn the tables on him.

12:03.287 --> 12:04.724
No strings.

12:07.030 --> 12:09.206
- You're bluffing.

12:10.381 --> 12:12.383
- Where you first
dropped me off.

12:12.427 --> 12:13.863
5:00 p.m.

12:19.826 --> 12:21.958
- Don't say
you're considering it.

12:24.569 --> 12:27.137
They butchered him, boss.

12:29.139 --> 12:31.272
They left his body to bloat
in the desert.

12:31.315 --> 12:34.275
Do you understand?
All we have to do is leave.

12:34.318 --> 12:38.235
You've got your list of names.
You've got the upper hand.

12:38.279 --> 12:41.151
God damn it.
You're sentimental, boss.

12:41.195 --> 12:44.372
It's gonna get us both killed.

12:44.415 --> 12:47.244
- Sentimental, yes.

12:47.288 --> 12:48.768
You, Sidney,

12:48.811 --> 12:51.118
you are a sentient
scouring brush

12:51.161 --> 12:53.120
with fingernails for brains.

12:53.163 --> 12:57.080
You reek of rum and failure.

12:59.039 --> 13:01.084
The only thing more repugnant

13:01.128 --> 13:03.043
than the sight of your face
in front of me

13:03.086 --> 13:06.481
is the thought of interviewing
another sad piece of gristle

13:06.524 --> 13:08.570
to take your place!

13:08.613 --> 13:11.268
So, yes, I'm sentimental.

13:11.312 --> 13:15.969
♪

13:16.012 --> 13:18.101
Do you know
what you are, Sidney?

13:20.234 --> 13:22.018
Expendable.

13:22.062 --> 13:25.108
[rumbling echoing]

13:29.634 --> 13:33.116
- Eve, I didn't--I didn't know
how old those twins were.

13:33.160 --> 13:36.206
Hell, I-I didn't even know
they were twins!

13:36.250 --> 13:38.992
- They looked
exactly alike, Tony.

13:39.035 --> 13:42.473
Your driver picked them up
from field hockey practice.

13:42.517 --> 13:45.476
- I would also like to say,
in my defense,

13:45.520 --> 13:48.871
it was a hookah pipe.

13:48.915 --> 13:51.308
Hoo-kah.

13:51.352 --> 13:55.051
I-I believe the drugs
to be cultural,

13:55.095 --> 13:57.358
not--not recreational.

13:57.401 --> 14:00.100
[quirky music]

14:00.143 --> 14:01.492
God damn it!
This ain't right!

14:01.536 --> 14:04.974
- Zip it, Tony.

14:05.018 --> 14:07.411
The pictures in that folder
are more than enough

14:07.455 --> 14:08.935
to put you in jail.

14:08.978 --> 14:10.762
So here's
what's gonna happen--

14:10.806 --> 14:12.590
you resign...

14:12.634 --> 14:14.114
today.

14:14.157 --> 14:15.506
You head over to your office,

14:15.550 --> 14:17.987
and you pack up
your little golf balls.

14:18.031 --> 14:20.381
Pack 'em nice and tight.

14:20.424 --> 14:23.384
It's time to get back
to selling used cars

14:23.427 --> 14:26.822
and begging for dry hand jobs
in highway rest stops...

14:26.866 --> 14:28.215
[pounds desk]
Or whatever it was

14:28.258 --> 14:31.044
you used to do before you
started using City Hall

14:31.087 --> 14:33.133
as your personal brothel!

14:35.962 --> 14:40.140
[laughs]

14:40.183 --> 14:44.361
Yeah, you are done.

14:44.405 --> 14:45.754
No more chances.

14:45.797 --> 14:47.495
Mm-mm.

14:47.538 --> 14:49.845
Men like you always think
you deserve chances.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.586
[scoffs]

14:51.629 --> 14:53.588
- What...

14:53.631 --> 14:55.459
are you?

14:55.503 --> 14:59.159
- I'm the scariest thing
in the world, Tony.

14:59.202 --> 15:01.074
I'm a lady with a job.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.468
And I'm good at it.

15:10.910 --> 15:12.737
[door opens,
cell phone buzzes]

15:12.781 --> 15:14.652
[door closes]

15:17.220 --> 15:20.310
Hey.
Got my message?

15:20.354 --> 15:22.225
Good.

15:22.269 --> 15:24.880
Let's meet and talk.

15:24.924 --> 15:28.362
[ice rattling]

15:34.194 --> 15:37.980
[monitor beeping]

15:38.024 --> 15:40.156
- Here.

15:40.200 --> 15:42.767
Don't tell the nurse.

15:42.811 --> 15:45.248
- [laughs]

15:49.035 --> 15:50.688
- [sighs]

15:50.732 --> 15:53.126
You were the only one
trying to tell me the truth.

15:54.954 --> 15:57.130
- [groans]

15:57.173 --> 15:59.306
- From the beginning.

16:00.742 --> 16:03.353
- Doing this 50 years.

16:05.007 --> 16:09.403
People only ever believe
what they want.

16:10.621 --> 16:13.015
- Why keep at it?

16:13.059 --> 16:16.714
- Same reason
I look at pretty girls' asses--

16:16.758 --> 16:18.368
see if the muscle still works.

16:18.412 --> 16:20.414
- Don't play dumb, Freddie.

16:20.457 --> 16:23.243
Do you know
who killed my sister?

16:23.286 --> 16:26.115
- Do you?
- Yes.

16:26.159 --> 16:28.422
The only thing I don't know

16:28.465 --> 16:29.989
is what you got
from your secret source

16:30.032 --> 16:31.512
in the department.

16:34.384 --> 16:36.256
It was Strucker, wasn't it?

16:38.780 --> 16:40.782
[tense music]

16:40.825 --> 16:43.698
He knew.

16:43.741 --> 16:46.309
He told you.

16:46.353 --> 16:49.791
And he was going to tell me.

16:49.834 --> 16:52.750
That's why he had to go...

16:52.794 --> 16:54.665
and why you got spooked.

16:54.709 --> 16:57.059
♪

16:57.103 --> 16:58.843
- What are you gonna do
about it?

16:58.887 --> 17:00.976
- Mm-mm.

17:01.020 --> 17:03.892
No, Freddie.

17:03.935 --> 17:05.850
What are you gonna do?

17:05.894 --> 17:12.727
♪

17:21.344 --> 17:23.912
- I can't print this.
They'd never let me.

17:23.955 --> 17:25.218
- Who'll stop you?

17:25.261 --> 17:28.047
♪

17:28.090 --> 17:30.701
Time's up on the Staghornes...

17:30.745 --> 17:32.921
the Chief.

17:32.964 --> 17:36.403
Choice is yours, Chuckles.

17:36.446 --> 17:39.754
Why not be the one
to tip the hourglass?

17:39.797 --> 17:46.804
♪

17:46.848 --> 17:50.286
[frantic clicking]

17:51.722 --> 17:53.115
[sign clicks]

17:54.290 --> 17:57.206
[dog barking]

17:57.250 --> 18:00.296
[growling]

18:04.126 --> 18:07.042
[funky music]

18:07.086 --> 18:09.131
♪

18:09.175 --> 18:10.132
[gun cocks]

18:10.176 --> 18:17.313
♪

18:21.970 --> 18:23.885
- I saw that press conference.

18:23.928 --> 18:25.800
What the hell is your angle?

18:25.843 --> 18:29.456
- My angle is trying to save
your sorry ass, Gene.

18:30.631 --> 18:32.415
- I tried to murder you.
- Bygones.

18:32.459 --> 18:34.374
After all, I tried
to murder you right back.

18:34.417 --> 18:36.593
Let me just get you a soda.

18:36.637 --> 18:38.682
- Tell me one reason
why I shouldn't finish you off

18:38.726 --> 18:40.119
right here and now?

18:40.162 --> 18:42.469
- Because, Captain Colder,
I've got what you want...

18:44.210 --> 18:46.429
A way out.

18:46.473 --> 18:47.474
And you're the only one

18:47.517 --> 18:49.954
who can help me get
what I want.

18:49.998 --> 18:51.956
So let's fix this...

18:52.000 --> 18:53.828
together...

18:53.871 --> 18:55.743
for the both of us.

18:58.746 --> 19:00.182
What do you say?

19:00.226 --> 19:07.363
♪

19:09.844 --> 19:11.715
- I'm listening.

19:11.759 --> 19:13.282
[tense music]

19:13.326 --> 19:16.720
- You okay?

19:16.764 --> 19:18.679
Take a drink.

19:18.722 --> 19:20.115
- No, thanks.

19:20.159 --> 19:22.639
♪

19:22.683 --> 19:24.989
Liquor and old Clyde
don't really mix.

19:25.033 --> 19:27.731
♪

19:27.775 --> 19:30.256
- You can handle this.
- Uh-huh.

19:30.299 --> 19:34.129
[breathes deeply]

19:34.173 --> 19:35.565
[car brakes squeak]

19:35.609 --> 19:38.829
[Ivan Marinov's
"Mefistolfele: Largo"]

19:38.873 --> 19:40.875
[engine revs]

19:40.918 --> 19:44.008
[orchestra fanfare]

19:44.052 --> 19:50.972
♪

20:03.550 --> 20:05.552
- Something's changed.

20:10.034 --> 20:12.863
I knew you'd make it out
of the desert, by the way.

20:14.648 --> 20:18.086
I'm very proud of you, Jake.

20:18.129 --> 20:21.045
You were always my best boy.

20:21.089 --> 20:22.569
- Don't talk to him.

20:22.612 --> 20:24.919
Only to me.

20:24.962 --> 20:26.355
- My dear, I'm just glad

20:26.399 --> 20:28.444
he's found a new
commanding officer.

20:28.488 --> 20:30.359
[tense music]

20:30.403 --> 20:32.840
He means a great deal to me.

20:32.883 --> 20:35.234
Such a raw talent.

20:35.277 --> 20:36.887
No control.

20:36.931 --> 20:40.108
♪

20:40.151 --> 20:41.849
- This is a recording

20:41.892 --> 20:45.200
of the senator conspiring
to blackmail,

20:45.244 --> 20:47.985
condoning a murder.

20:48.029 --> 20:50.466
Whoever has this controls him.

20:50.510 --> 20:52.773
Give me what I want,
and it's yours.

20:52.816 --> 20:55.776
♪

20:55.819 --> 20:57.081
Gene Colder.

20:57.125 --> 20:59.867
♪

20:59.910 --> 21:02.826
- [laughs]

21:02.870 --> 21:05.089
Oh, my.

21:05.133 --> 21:08.136
Are we sure Gene Colder
is worth all this effort?

21:08.179 --> 21:10.356
For the purposes of revenge,

21:10.399 --> 21:13.097
any warm body would do.

21:13.141 --> 21:14.447
Maybe Sid would suffice.

21:14.490 --> 21:17.580
We could set it up
as a suicide.

21:17.624 --> 21:21.932
You were always magic
at suicide notes, Jacob.

21:21.976 --> 21:25.240
♪

21:25.284 --> 21:28.417
- Colder or nothing.

21:28.461 --> 21:32.029
- Something has changed.

21:32.073 --> 21:35.119
And it's you, Ms. Dill.

21:35.163 --> 21:36.730
You know this world,

21:36.773 --> 21:39.994
and you know your place in it.

21:40.037 --> 21:42.866
I admire that.

21:42.910 --> 21:46.174
You should stick
with this one, Jacob.

21:46.217 --> 21:48.002
You might learn something.

21:54.182 --> 21:56.837
We have a deal, Ms. Dill.

22:06.020 --> 22:08.631
Now, as for actually corralling
Gene Colder,

22:08.675 --> 22:09.980
that might take some time--

22:10.024 --> 22:12.200
[gunshot]

22:12.243 --> 22:15.203
[ominous music]

22:15.246 --> 22:22.341
♪

22:32.046 --> 22:33.961
Dear boy...

22:34.004 --> 22:35.310
there you are.

22:35.354 --> 22:36.659
We were just talking about you.

22:36.703 --> 22:38.095
You do have a knack

22:38.139 --> 22:40.402
for showing up
when least expected, don't you?

22:40.446 --> 22:41.838
Still, take a seat,

22:41.882 --> 22:44.014
and we can discuss how we're
gonna figure out this--

22:44.058 --> 22:46.190
[gunshot]

22:46.234 --> 22:53.154
♪

22:59.465 --> 23:01.728
- I need you to listen, okay?

23:03.251 --> 23:05.819
[echoing]
Listen.

23:05.862 --> 23:09.692
- [echoing]
I'm listening.

23:09.736 --> 23:13.000
- [echoing]
I'm not a bad man.

23:13.043 --> 23:15.089
[normal audio]
That man there?

23:15.132 --> 23:17.439
He's the monster.

23:17.483 --> 23:19.180
He's done awful things to me.

23:19.223 --> 23:22.226
- And what about you, Gene?

23:22.270 --> 23:26.405
What about the things you did?
- Listen to me, Allegra.

23:26.448 --> 23:29.451
I loved your sister so much.

23:29.495 --> 23:31.105
She understood me.

23:31.148 --> 23:33.586
And if I would've just
done the job I came here for--

23:33.629 --> 23:35.065
- Killing Jake?

23:35.109 --> 23:37.241
- Then we would've had
a perfect life forever.

23:37.285 --> 23:39.548
- But you murdered her.

23:39.592 --> 23:41.724
- The woman who betrayed me,

23:41.768 --> 23:44.292
she was someone else entirely.

23:44.335 --> 23:45.511
She had your sister's face,

23:45.554 --> 23:48.209
but something inside her
had twisted.

23:48.252 --> 23:50.080
That woman had to die

23:50.124 --> 23:52.169
so I could keep loving
my Felicity.

23:52.213 --> 23:55.564
Don't you understand?
I still love her!

23:55.608 --> 23:57.436
- She knew what you were.

23:57.479 --> 23:59.176
What you are.

23:59.220 --> 24:02.266
A dirty cop, a coward...

24:02.310 --> 24:03.529
- No.
- And a killer.

24:03.572 --> 24:05.792
- No. No!

24:05.835 --> 24:08.969
For God sakes, Allegra,
it's not that complicated.

24:09.012 --> 24:10.623
I'm a good guy!

24:10.666 --> 24:14.322
And now that I fixed this--
[gunshot]

24:14.365 --> 24:17.456
[grunting and wheezing]

24:23.984 --> 24:26.682
- You know, he talked
too damn much.

24:26.726 --> 24:29.903
- You had no right to do that.

24:29.946 --> 24:31.600
- I took that weight from you.

24:31.644 --> 24:34.516
- It wasn't yours to take!

24:34.560 --> 24:36.649
- Raytek!

24:36.692 --> 24:39.303
[whimpering]

24:39.347 --> 24:41.523
Raytek!

24:42.829 --> 24:45.745
[footsteps approaching]

24:45.788 --> 24:48.965
[dramatic music]

24:49.009 --> 24:53.404
♪

24:53.448 --> 24:55.450
- Eve...

24:55.494 --> 24:57.539
this ain't got nothing to do
with you.

24:57.583 --> 24:59.889
♪

24:59.933 --> 25:01.630
- Raytek.

25:01.674 --> 25:03.763
Raytek.
Where were you?

25:03.806 --> 25:06.505
You said
you were gonna cover me!

25:06.548 --> 25:08.594
- Cover him?
Eve!

25:08.637 --> 25:11.074
[scoffs]
He's the bomber.

25:11.118 --> 25:12.554
- The first one.

25:12.598 --> 25:14.513
I only did the first one!

25:14.556 --> 25:15.644
- Oh, yeah?

25:15.688 --> 25:17.472
Well, then who set
the second one?

25:17.516 --> 25:20.519
- I don't know!

25:20.562 --> 25:23.173
- I know.

25:23.217 --> 25:26.046
It was her.

25:26.089 --> 25:27.177
- Guilty.

25:27.221 --> 25:29.092
[gunshot]

25:35.621 --> 25:37.013
- What did you do?

25:37.057 --> 25:39.407
- What did I do?
Look over there.

25:39.450 --> 25:40.800
That's Captain Gene Colder

25:40.843 --> 25:42.976
lying in his own blood
and piss.

25:43.019 --> 25:46.153
The best goddamn homicide cop
this town's ever seen.

25:46.196 --> 25:48.547
He died heroically

25:48.590 --> 25:51.114
in a gunfight
with Clyde Brattle.

25:51.158 --> 25:53.203
You have any idea
how hard I have to work

25:53.247 --> 25:56.119
so ungrateful shits like you
can stay clean?

25:56.163 --> 25:59.035
Why don't you go on
and have another drink?

25:59.079 --> 26:01.516
Let us girls
work this thing out.

26:01.560 --> 26:03.170
Come on, sit.

26:08.610 --> 26:13.049
♪

26:13.093 --> 26:15.574
How'd you figure it?
- Wasn't that hard.

26:15.617 --> 26:18.751
Military records.

26:18.794 --> 26:20.230
Your partner here--

26:20.274 --> 26:21.580
- Ex-partner.

26:21.623 --> 26:23.625
♪

26:23.669 --> 26:26.889
- [sighs] She ever talk
about her Army days?

26:26.933 --> 26:29.152
She was in munitions.

26:29.196 --> 26:31.198
Ordnance disassembly
and disposal,

26:31.241 --> 26:33.853
which means she knew
exactly how to set the bomb

26:33.896 --> 26:35.637
in Strucker's car quickly...

26:35.681 --> 26:37.857
♪

26:37.900 --> 26:39.728
And how to tightrope-walk
across a minefield

26:39.772 --> 26:42.122
like this town.

26:42.165 --> 26:44.254
After Colder
killed my sister...

26:44.298 --> 26:46.256
♪

26:46.300 --> 26:48.911
You needed to keep the heat
off him.

26:48.955 --> 26:51.087
If he got popped for murder,
he'd flip on Brattle

26:51.131 --> 26:53.089
and you'd lose your chance
to make headlines,

26:53.133 --> 26:56.049
by catching him.

26:56.092 --> 26:58.791
So you blew up
poor Calvin Strucker...

26:58.834 --> 27:02.795
♪

27:02.838 --> 27:05.928
The only other cop who
suspected what you were up to

27:05.972 --> 27:10.063
and who knew about
Felicity's secret apartment.

27:10.106 --> 27:13.501
Plus, you had Floyd Ferness,
an ex with anger issues,

27:13.544 --> 27:16.330
all ready to frame up.

27:16.373 --> 27:19.463
Were you trying to kill me
that night with Strucker?

27:19.507 --> 27:21.814
Or would that
have been a bonus?

27:21.857 --> 27:23.467
- You little bitch.

27:23.511 --> 27:26.296
- Shh.

27:26.340 --> 27:29.691
We're talking.

27:29.735 --> 27:31.737
- Allegra...

27:31.780 --> 27:34.478
this town's been traumatized,

27:34.522 --> 27:36.829
beaten down.

27:36.872 --> 27:39.658
It doesn't need a bath.

27:39.701 --> 27:42.051
It needs a cleansing fire.

27:42.095 --> 27:45.315
Felicity understood.
She knew the goal.

27:45.359 --> 27:48.884
♪

27:48.928 --> 27:51.800
- Did she know the risks?

27:51.844 --> 27:54.150
- I loved your sister.

27:54.194 --> 27:56.413
She reminded me of myself
when I was younger--

27:56.457 --> 27:57.850
plucky...

27:57.893 --> 27:59.112
full of so much hope,

27:59.155 --> 28:02.245
she damn near floated
off the ground.

28:02.289 --> 28:03.899
Couple months back,
she came to me

28:03.943 --> 28:06.685
with tears in her eyes.

28:06.728 --> 28:09.383
She'd messed up, she said.

28:09.426 --> 28:11.515
Had a few too many.

28:11.559 --> 28:14.344
Slept with Gene Colder...

28:14.388 --> 28:15.781
her boss,

28:15.824 --> 28:18.609
a married man.

28:18.653 --> 28:20.829
I told her not to worry.

28:20.873 --> 28:23.571
It happens.

28:23.614 --> 28:26.835
Ain't that right?

28:26.879 --> 28:28.837
[chuckles]
Then she started telling me

28:28.881 --> 28:30.752
other things
about Gene, you know?

28:30.796 --> 28:33.102
All the money
he had lying around,

28:33.146 --> 28:34.756
weapons,

28:34.800 --> 28:38.760
a particular interest
in that jackass right there.

28:38.804 --> 28:40.849
- She figured it out.
All of it.

28:40.893 --> 28:42.982
And instead of doing your job,

28:43.025 --> 28:46.725
you convinced her to fake
a relationship with Colder.

28:46.768 --> 28:48.291
The longer she kept him
distracted,

28:48.335 --> 28:52.426
the more likely Brattle would
come to kill Jake himself.

28:52.469 --> 28:55.734
You didn't love her.

28:55.777 --> 28:57.213
You used her.

28:57.257 --> 28:59.607
- When are you gonna stop
treating Felicity like a kid?

28:59.650 --> 29:02.218
Huh?

29:02.262 --> 29:03.437
She volunteered!

29:03.480 --> 29:06.179
Hell, she was eager.

29:06.222 --> 29:08.007
When Colder gave her
the dirty money

29:08.050 --> 29:11.227
for the complex,
I told her to go with it, yeah.

29:11.271 --> 29:14.100
I also told her
to get her own place,

29:14.143 --> 29:15.449
above the tamale shop,

29:15.492 --> 29:17.320
so she wouldn't lose herself
completely.

29:17.364 --> 29:18.539
- Hey, Pick?

29:18.582 --> 29:22.369
I swear I didn't know
about any of this.

29:22.412 --> 29:24.632
- Of course you didn't...

29:24.675 --> 29:27.243
'cause you never asked.

29:27.287 --> 29:29.028
You're the hungriest,
greediest boy in the world,

29:29.071 --> 29:31.465
and you always expect someone
else to pick up the tab.

29:31.508 --> 29:33.641
- Allegra, there's a way
for all three of us

29:33.684 --> 29:36.383
to walk out of here happy.

29:36.426 --> 29:40.909
I delivered Gene Colder to you,
so you got your revenge.

29:40.953 --> 29:44.391
We blackmail the senator,
Jake will stay out of jail.

29:44.434 --> 29:46.306
And with Big Tony gone,

29:46.349 --> 29:50.353
I'll get to fix
this broken town.

29:50.397 --> 29:51.920
Don't be foolish.

29:51.964 --> 29:53.617
- Pick...

29:53.661 --> 29:57.230
♪

29:57.273 --> 30:00.973
- Ask her
about your land, Jake.

30:01.016 --> 30:02.844
She took it...

30:02.888 --> 30:04.063
all of it.

30:04.106 --> 30:05.847
This building, too.

30:05.891 --> 30:09.155
Horse-traded it to my bosses
for her future.

30:09.198 --> 30:11.810
Your shoeless lawyer
took the deeds when she left.

30:11.853 --> 30:12.854
It was pretty easy

30:12.898 --> 30:14.813
for my lawyer
to figure out how.

30:14.856 --> 30:16.902
- I'll break your neck.

30:16.945 --> 30:18.947
- You won't even break a sweat.

30:18.991 --> 30:20.731
- Was it worth it?

30:20.775 --> 30:22.777
- Hell, yes, honey.

30:22.821 --> 30:24.735
It was worth it.

30:24.779 --> 30:26.868
It's always worth it
if you win.

30:26.912 --> 30:34.006
♪

30:37.444 --> 30:39.315
- No, Pick!

30:39.359 --> 30:40.751
Brattle didn't deserve
that recording,

30:40.795 --> 30:42.362
and neither does she.

30:42.405 --> 30:44.973
- You hung my sister out
to dry.

30:45.017 --> 30:47.671
- [scoffs]
- Both of you.

30:47.715 --> 30:50.849
Abused her youth...

30:50.892 --> 30:54.330
her optimism...

30:54.374 --> 30:55.679
her trust.

30:55.723 --> 30:59.683
♪

30:59.727 --> 31:01.207
All of you are guilty.

31:01.250 --> 31:03.687
And now you think
that winning will make it okay.

31:03.731 --> 31:06.865
♪

31:06.908 --> 31:08.823
If this is what you want
so badly...

31:08.867 --> 31:13.523
♪

31:13.567 --> 31:15.351
You deserve each other.

31:15.395 --> 31:21.227
♪

31:23.490 --> 31:25.492
[both grunting]

31:25.535 --> 31:28.451
[funky music]

31:28.495 --> 31:35.241
♪

31:49.081 --> 31:52.780
[frantic clicking]

31:52.823 --> 31:54.956
[sign clicks]

31:55.000 --> 31:58.090
- [groaning]

32:07.882 --> 32:09.971
[grunts]

32:15.498 --> 32:18.458
[laughs]

32:20.286 --> 32:21.983
[car beeps,
engine turns over]

32:22.027 --> 32:23.158
No!

32:25.073 --> 32:27.989
[dramatic music]

32:28.033 --> 32:35.170
♪

32:38.173 --> 32:40.132
[elevator bell dings]

32:40.175 --> 32:43.526
♪

32:43.570 --> 32:45.920
- Ms. Dill...

32:45.964 --> 32:48.967
I'm pleased
you're still with us.

32:49.010 --> 32:52.579
- Can it, Cyrus.

32:52.622 --> 32:54.798
It's all on tape.

32:54.842 --> 32:57.845
Everything you said
in that room yesterday.

32:57.888 --> 32:59.847
Brattle's dead...

32:59.890 --> 33:02.676
and so is the senator's
presidential campaign.

33:02.719 --> 33:05.853
- Allegra, blackmail
isn't your strong suit.

33:05.896 --> 33:07.855
- Doesn't need to be.

33:07.898 --> 33:14.993
♪

33:32.140 --> 33:33.750
- What do you want?

33:33.794 --> 33:37.667
- [breathes deeply]

33:37.711 --> 33:40.366
I want to be left alone.

33:40.409 --> 33:42.063
And if you give me what I want,

33:42.107 --> 33:44.544
you have nothing
to worry about.

33:44.587 --> 33:48.026
But if anyone comes after me,
the audio will be released.

33:48.069 --> 33:51.333
And if that happens...

33:51.377 --> 33:52.726
the only time
the senator's name

33:52.769 --> 33:54.902
will get mentioned
inside the Beltway

33:54.945 --> 33:58.471
will be in regards
to sentencing guidelines.

33:58.514 --> 34:01.169
- The FBI is already en route.

34:01.213 --> 34:03.389
They're expecting
to arrest Brattle

34:03.432 --> 34:04.868
and Spivey.

34:04.912 --> 34:08.350
I'm to believe you have a copy
of this recording secured?

34:08.394 --> 34:11.353
- I need help.

34:11.397 --> 34:14.182
No, not there.
It's not safe.

